[Santa Fe Province is in northern Argentina, on the west side of the Parana river. It is cattle country; see: http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/americas/argentina_pol96.jpg. For Totoras, go to: http://www.fallingrain.com/world/AR/21/Totoras.html.

Anthrax is truly sporadic in Santa Fe Province with 1 outbreak in 2008, 1 in 2010, and 4 in 2014.

Most anthrax activity in Argentina is in the pampas, Buenos Aires Province, and so in the outer provinces there can be a lack of awareness of the local incidence and risks accruing. And in conjunction, various scavenging birds take advantage of the situation; see: Miguel D Saggese, et al. First detection of _Bacillus anthracis_ in feces of free ranging raptors from central Argentina. Journal of Wildlife Diseases 2007; 43: 136-141. - Mod.MHJ

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4175335,1169.]
